.SH "NAME"
MooseX::Storage::Format::Storable \- A Storable serialization role
.SH "VERSION"
.IX Header "VERSION"
version 0.53
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 3
\&  package Point;
\&  use Moose;
\&  use MooseX::Storage;
\&
\&  with Storage(\*(Aqformat\*(Aq => \*(AqStorable\*(Aq);
\&
\&  has \*(Aqx\*(Aq => (is => \*(Aqrw\*(Aq, isa => \*(AqInt\*(Aq);
\&  has \*(Aqy\*(Aq => (is => \*(Aqrw\*(Aq, isa => \*(AqInt\*(Aq);
\&
\&  1;
\&
\&  my $p = Point\->new(x => 10, y => 10);
\&
\&  ## methods to freeze/thaw into
\&  ## a specified serialization format
\&
\&  # pack the class with Storable
\&  my $storable_data = $p\->freeze();
\&
\&  # unpack the storable data into the class
\&  my $p2 = Point\->thaw($storable_data);
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This module will \f(CW\*(C`thaw\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`freeze\*(C'\fR Moose classes using Storable. It
uses \f(CW\*(C`Storable::nfreeze\*(C'\fR by default so that it can be easily used
in \s-1IPC\s0 scenarios across machines or just locally.
.PP
One important thing to note is that this module does not mix well
with the \s-1IO\s0 modules. The structures that \f(CW\*(C`freeze\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`thaw\*(C'\fR deal with
are Storable's memory representation, and (as far as I know) that
is not easily just written onto a file. If you want file based
serialization with Storable, the please look at the
MooseX::Storage::IO::StorableFile role instead.
.SH "METHODS"
.IX Header "METHODS"
.IP "\fBfreeze\fR" 4
.IX Item "freeze"
.PD 0
